title: Left Menu Navigation Items
content: The Left Menu in Globe3 ERP Fixed Assets Manager comprises: Setup, Process, Depreciation, Disposal, and Reports.

title: Fixed Asset Manager Overview
content: As of Thursday, 19 Sep 2024, there are 14 Registered Fixed Assets, 2 Disposed Fixed Assets, and 12 Unregistered Fixed Assets.

title: Define Fixed Asset Tiers
content:
Navigate to Applications > Finance > Fixed Asset Manager > Setup > Fixed Asset Group.
Define each tier with a unique code and description.
Fixed Asset Manager adopts a 3-tier management of assets: Fixed Asset Group (first tier, grouped by nature or type), Fixed Asset Category (second tier, broken down from group), and Fixed Asset Class (third tier, broken down from category and linked to GL number for cost, accumulated depreciation, and depreciation expense).

title: Fixed Asset Group UI Fields
content: When setting up a Fixed Asset Group, the UI includes fields for 'FX Code', 'Fixed Assets Main Group Description', and 'Set As Default'. Actions include 'NEW', 'LIST', 'ADMIN', 'EDIT', and 'SAVE'.

title: Fixed Asset Category UI Fields
content: When setting up a Fixed Asset Category, the UI allows selecting a 'Fixed Asset Group' (e.g., T06 Computing) and defining a 'Code' and 'Description'. It also includes a 'Set As Default' option and 'SAVE' action.

title: Fixed Asset Class UI Fields
content: When setting up a Fixed Asset Class, the UI allows selecting a 'Fixed Asset Category' (e.g., F35 Furniture/Fitting) and defining a 'Code' and 'Description' (e.g., Air-Conditioner). It requires linking GL numbers for 'Fixed Asset Cost', 'Accumulated Depreciation' (e.g., 170200100), and 'Depreciation Expense' (e.g., 610700200). It also includes a 'Set As Default' option and 'SAVE' action.

title: Define Fixed Asset Adjustments
content: Fixed Asset Adjustments are used for fixed assets with Net Book Value (NBV) to register them in the system. The following fields are required before registering a fixed asset: Auto SYS Number (system generated or manually entered), Purchase Date, Name (supplier), Business Unit/Cost Center, Acctnum - Cost (fixed asset at cost account number), Currency, Quantity, Unit Price (Forex), FA Cost (Forex), and FA Cost (Local).

title: Fixed Asset Adjustments UI Fields Example
content: An example of Fixed Asset Adjustments fields and their values: Auto SYS Number: FAJ1011, Purchase Date: 01/01/2019, Name: Addey Technology Limited, Business Unit: L005, Acctnum - Cost: 1701001.00 FURNITURE & FITTINGS, Currency: SGD (Base), Forex Rate: 1.00000000, Quantity: 1, Unit Price (Forex): 120000.00, FA Cost (Forex): 120000.00, FA Cost (Local): 120000.00.

title: Define Sub Location for Fixed Asset
content:
Navigate to Applications > Finance > Fixed Asset Manager > Setup > Sub Location.
Click 'new' to define sub locations from the main location where the fixed asset has been placed.
Enter the name of the sub location (e.g., SL-105) and save it. Options include 'Set As Default'.

title: Register Fixed Assets
content:
Navigate to Applications > Finance > Fixed Asset Manager > Process > Register.
System will list down assets pending for registration from Fixed Asset Adjustment or a purchase Invoice when you click 'new'.
Select an Asset to register.
Enter the required field values: FA Class, Currency and Rate, Use Date, Useful Life (Month), Status, Acctnum - Cost, Acctnum - Accum Depr, Acctnum - Depr Expense, Depreciation Method, Asset Code, Asset Description, FA Cost (SGD), Accum Depr (SGD), Residual Value (SGD), Location, Sub-Location, Sub-Loc Info, and Quantity.
Click 'submit' after all field values have been entered.

title: Depreciate Fixed Assets
content:
Navigate to Applications > Finance > Fixed Asset Manager > Depreciation > Depreciate.
Select the appropriate period for depreciation (e.g., P01 (31-Jan-2011)).
Click 'Next'. System will list all active status items with remaining useful life.
When clicking 'Next' again, a preview of the journals to be posted on the system will be displayed for confirmation.
Review the depreciation preview table, which includes Code, Description, Method, Last Date, Cost Basis, Realizable, Depreciable Cost, Prev Depr, This Depr, and NBV for each asset.
Review the journal preview table, which includes Acctnum, Description, BU, Project, Debit, and Credit.
Click 'Save' to confirm and post the depreciation journals.

title: Dispose Fixed Assets
content:
Navigate to Applications > Finance > Fixed Asset Manager > Disposal > Disposal.
Enter the Disposal Date (DMY, e.g., 31 01 2011) and Reason (e.g., Disposal).
Optionally, use a 'Search String' or 'Disposal By Quantity'.
Click 'Next'. System will list assets available for disposal.
Select the asset(s) to dispose.
Review the disposal preview table, which includes Asset Code, Description, Expiry Date, FA Cost, Accum Depr, Book Value, and Residual Value for each asset.
Click 'Next' again to see a preview of the accounting entries before confirming.
Review the journal preview table, which includes Account, Description, BU, Project, Debit, and Credit.
Click 'Save' to confirm. The status of the Asset Code will be changed to 'retired'.

title: Generate Fixed Asset Listing Report
content:
Navigate to Applications > Finance > Fixed Asset Manager > Reports > Fixed Asset Listing.
Generate the Fixed Asset Listing Report to view the current book value status of each asset.
The report displays details such as Auto Number, Supplier, Asset Class, Asset Description, Use Date, Status, Expiry Date, FA Cost, Accum Depr, Book Value, and Residual Value, grouped by Asset Class with Sub-Totals.
